1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:20,000
Kitten Economics Episode 1: Opportunity Cost.

2
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Welcome back. Today we learn one core economics idea with kittens.

3
00:00:45,000 --> 00:01:15,000
Milo the kitten has to choose between fish, playtime, and a nap.

4
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:45,000
He learns that every yes quietly means no to something else. Opportunity cost is not what you paid; it is the best thing you gave up.

5
00:01:45,000 --> 00:02:10,000
In daily life, this explains why scrolling for one hour costs you more than time: it may cost your workout, your focus, or your sleep. Use three questions before any decision: What is my best alternative? Will it still matter in a week? Am I choosing short-term comfort or long-term value?.

6
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Recap: Opportunity Cost. Use this rule in real decisions. Comment: More Kitten Economics.
